From 057e0b2bcbd507482cf29184936c23d79876cbc5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 22:14:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Revert: remove /onboarding from publicPaths
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Rolls back the publicPaths change from the signup-flow-fix PR, which
was incorrect. The onboarding flow requires authenticated Base44
users — every step handler (handleMemberTypeNext, handlePlanNext,
handleNDAAccept, handleNonCompeteAccept) calls base44.auth.updateMe
which 403s for unauthenticated visitors.

Confirmed live: after the signup-flow-fix deployed, unauthenticated
visitors clicking 'I'm a TC' reached /onboarding but the page never
rendered — it hit cascading 403s on app-state check, /me, and app
settings endpoints. Users were stuck on an error-flooded blank page.

The correct flow was already in place before the bad PR:

  1. Unauthenticated visitor clicks 'I'm a TC' on landing
  2. Navigates to /onboarding?type=tc
  3. App.jsx sees /onboarding not in publicPaths
  4. navigateToLogin() redirects to Base44's /login?from_url=...
  5. Base44's login page renders with:
       - Continue with Google
       - Email + password form
       - 'Need an account? Sign up' link
  6. New users sign up, existing users sign in
  7. Base44 returns user authenticated to the from_url
  8. App.jsx now has a valid user → /onboarding renders
  9. Step handlers work because user is authenticated

My earlier analysis missed this because I only read Onboarding.jsx's
initial loadUserState (which does handle null user via try/catch)
and didn't trace through the step-advance handlers, which all
require auth. Won't make that mistake again.

Also replaced the misleading 'signup happens inside onboarding'
comment with an accurate one explaining WHY /onboarding stays
private — should prevent a future contributor from making the same
mistake.

Files (1):
  - src/App.jsx (+19/-13)

Verification:
  - npm run lint: 0 errors
  - npm run build: succeeds
  - Dropdown emoji cleanup from the same original PR is preserved
    (that was a good change — only App.jsx needed reverting)
---
 src/App.jsx | 32 +++++++++++++++++++-------------
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+), 13 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/App.jsx b/src/App.jsx
index 6dc6a3c..dbcb094 100644
--- a/src/App.jsx
+++ b/src/App.jsx
@@ -36,19 +36,26 @@ const AuthenticatedApp = () => {
   }
 
   // Paths accessible to unauthenticated visitors when the app's auth
-  // preflight returns auth_required. The landing page, partners page,
-  // and the onboarding form are the entry points for new users — they
-  // must be reachable without a Base44 account. The user will sign
-  // up / create their Base44 account as part of the onboarding flow
-  // itself (before Stripe checkout, which needs an account to attach
-  // the subscription to).
+  // preflight returns auth_required.
   //
-  // /onboarding was previously NOT in this list, which meant clicking
-  // 'I'm a TC' / 'Join as TC' on the landing page redirected
-  // unauthenticated visitors to Base44 login — a dead-end for people
-  // who don't yet have accounts. Added so the signup flow actually
-  // works for new users.
-  const publicPaths = ["/", "/partners", "/onboarding"];
+  // /onboarding is NOT in this list. Even though it's the destination
+  // of every landing-page CTA, unauthenticated users can't complete
+  // the flow — every step handler (handleMemberTypeNext,
+  // handlePlanNext, handleNDAAccept, etc.) calls base44.auth.updateMe
+  // which requires a valid session. Letting unauthenticated users
+  // reach /onboarding results in cascading 403s and a page that
+  // renders but can't advance.
+  //
+  // The correct flow for new users:
+  //   1. Click 'I'm a TC' → navigates to /onboarding?type=tc
+  //   2. App hits this branch: /onboarding not in publicPaths
+  //   3. navigateToLogin() redirects to Base44's login page
+  //   4. Base44's login page has 'Continue with Google' + email/password
+  //      + 'Need an account? Sign up' link
+  //   5. User signs up or signs in; Base44 preserves ?type=tc via from_url
+  //   6. User returns authenticated → /onboarding renders → step handlers
+  //      work because user is now authenticated.
+  const publicPaths = ["/", "/partners"];
   const currentPath = window.location.pathname;
 
   if (authError) {
@@ -60,7 +67,6 @@ const AuthenticatedApp = () => {
           <Routes>
             <Route path="/" element={<LandingPage user={null} />} />
             <Route path="/partners" element={<PartnersPage user={null} />} />
-            <Route path="/onboarding" element={<Onboarding />} />
             <Route path="*" element={<Navigate to="/" replace />} />
           </Routes>
         );
